<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Asgeir is confused by what he found in the woods.
Deliver the pristine crate to Asgeir.
I was out gathering lumber the other day when out of nowhere an arrow came whistling past my head. It wasn't until I regained my composure that I realized a letter had been tied to it.
Or rather, a map, which had a location not far from here marked on it.

It's likely a trap, but I suspect whatever danger may be lying in waiting will prove little trouble for a guest of Master Matoya. If you should find anything there, be it treasure or something else, I would gladly share it with you.
I know not where the map came from, but I'm curious to see what you find.
Ah, you are returned. Did you find anything?

A crate...?
It's filled with staves and bows. <gasp> It couldn't be...
A number of weapons were stolen from our storehouse but a few days past. We tracked them as far as we could, but their trail went cold at the border to Yx'Maja.
Do you suppose the keepers of Yx'Maja placed the crate there?
At any rate, we are grateful to have our weapons returned to us, though I can't imagine you would have need of them. But you must be compensated for your troubles. Here─this is for you.
